
[1]godliness

   GOD'LINESS, n. [from godly.] Piety; belief in God, and reverence for
   his character and laws.

   1. A religious life; a careful observance of the laws of God and
   performance of religious duties, proceeding from love and reverence for
   the divine character and commands; christian obedience.

   Godliness is profitable unto all things. 1 Tim. 4.

   2. Revelation; the system of christianity.

   Without controversy, great is the mystery of godliness;

   God was manifest in the flesh. l Tim.3.
